Lexicon data license
=====================

This directory contains compiled prediction data, NOT application code. The
files here are licensed separately from the rest of the repository (which is
under the Counter-Limitation License, see /LICENSE.md). The CLL does NOT apply
to these files.

Files
-----
  *.clex   word-frequency lexicons   — adapted from the unigram sources below
  *.cngm   word-bigram models        — adapted from the bigram sources below

These are *adaptations* (in the Creative Commons sense) of third-party data:
the words and counts have been filtered, re-ranked, quantized, and re-encoded
into the binary CLEX1 / CNGM1 formats by Tools/GenerateLexicons.swift.

Sources and licenses
--------------------
1. Unigrams (all languages) — hermitdave/FrequencyWords, derived from
   OpenSubtitles 2018.
   Licensed CC-BY-SA 4.0.  https://github.com/hermitdave/FrequencyWords
   License: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

2. Bigrams (all languages) — Tatoeba sentence exports.
   Licensed CC-BY 2.0 FR.  https://tatoeba.org/en/downloads
   License: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.0/fr/deed.en

Because the unigram source is CC-BY-SA 4.0, its ShareAlike term applies: the
adapted lexicon files in this directory (*.clex, and any *.cngm that mixes in
unigram-derived data) are likewise licensed under

    Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International (CC-BY-SA 4.0)

and may be redistributed under those terms. Changes were made (see above).
Attribution for all sources is also shown in the app's About screen.

DRM-free availability
---------------------
The App Store build of Clink is wrapped in Apple's FairPlay DRM. To ensure that
DRM does not restrict any recipient's CC-BY-SA 4.0 rights to this data, the
identical, unencumbered lexicon files are published DRM-free in the open-source
repository:

    https://github.com/anti-ltd/Clink-iOS/tree/main/Resources/Lexicons

Anyone may obtain, use, modify, and redistribute the lexicons from there under
CC-BY-SA 4.0, independent of the App Store distribution.
